\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.2}{\ignorespaces Meridian inflationary predictions in the $n_s$--$r$ plane. The $\alpha = 1$ K\"ahler modulus attractor (blue line, $N_* = 50$--$60$) predicts $n_s = 0.965 \pm 0.003$ and $r = 0.004 \pm 0.001$, consistent with Planck~2018 at $0.3\sigma $. The QQG framework (red shaded, $r \geq 0.01$) provides a sharp observational discriminant: Simons Observatory (${\sim }2027$, $\sigma (r) \sim 0.003$) and CMB-S4 (${\sim }2029$, $\sigma (r) \sim 0.001$) will cleanly separate the two predictions. LiteBIRD sensitivity shown as dotted line.}}{111}{figure.4.2}\protected@file@percent }
